President Obama has declared a state of emergency in New Jersey due to the conditions caused by Hurricane Irene. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to save lives and protect property. FEMA will have the authority to mobilize resources and equipment as needed. The federal government will provide 75 percent of funding for emergency protective measures. William L. Vogel has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.